South African gold output rose by 0.2 percent  in April from the figure in March, the Chamber of Mines, representing major  mining houses, said Monday.
April production was 50,658 kilograms compared with March's 50,557 kg, the  chamber said.
But April's total was 3.7 percent down on the 52,641 kg produced in the  same month in 1993, the figures showed.
The cumulative total for 1994 was 197,267 kg, 4.3 percent down on the  206,209 kg produced in the same period last year.
